{"componentChunkName":"component---src-blog-components-blog-post-template-jsx","path":"/blog/javascript-utility-libraries-you-should-know/","webpackCompilationHash":"016804984774e40a9a7e","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"f57b63cd-c612-53e2-b2eb-f90096f801d3","excerpt":"11 JavaScript Utility Libraries you Should Know in 2019 by Jonathan Saring Tip: Use Bit to discover and install specific functions from these libraries. You can…","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 725px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.48275862068966%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Javascript in 2018\"\n        title=\"Javascript in 2018\"\n        src=\"/static/10034bf987a1684453ff46fbb5f1d93b/8f35f/javascript-2018.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/10034bf987a1684453ff46fbb5f1d93b/942f4/javascript-2018.png 192w,\n/static/10034bf987a1684453ff46fbb5f1d93b/a7675/javascript-2018.png 384w,\n/static/10034bf987a1684453ff46fbb5f1d93b/8f35f/javascript-2018.png 725w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 725px) 100vw, 725px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://blog.bitsrc.io/11-javascript-utility-libraries-you-should-know-in-2018-3646fb31ade\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">11 JavaScript Utility Libraries you Should Know in 2019</a> by <a href=\"https://blog.bitsrc.io/@JonathanSaring\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Jonathan Saring</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Use <a href=\"https://github.com/teambit/bit\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bit</a> to discover and install specific functions from these libraries. You can find many of them in the Bit community, or share your own. Take a look.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"notes\"><a href=\"#notes\" aria-label=\"notes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Notes</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://insights.stackoverflow.com/survey/2018/#most-popular-technologies\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">2018 Insights</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.infoworld.com/article/3048833/brendan-eich-javascript-standard-library-will-stay-small.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"></a></p>\n<h3 id=\"1-underscore--lodash-dah\"><a href=\"#1-underscore--lodash-dah\" aria-label=\"1 underscore  lodash dah permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Underscore &#x26; Lodash (dah)</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/lodash/lodash\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lodash</a> - Lodash, NPM’s most downloaded and most dependent-upon package, was built to provide more consistent cross-environment iteration support for arrays, strings, objects, and arguments objects.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/jashkenas/underscore\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Underscore</a> - Underscore was built to provide utility functions for common tasks in Javascript.</p>\n<h3 id=\"2-ramda\"><a href=\"#2-ramda\" aria-label=\"2 ramda permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Ramda</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ramda/ramda\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ramda</a> - This JS utility library is designed for functional programming, making it easy to create functional pipelines that don’t mutate user data.</p>\n<p><strong>Worth Noting:</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/immutable-js/immutable-js\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Immutable.js</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"3-mathjs\"><a href=\"#3-mathjs\" aria-label=\"3 mathjs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3. MathJS</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/josdejong/mathjs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MathJS</a> - Math.js is an extensive math library for JavaScript and Node.js, which is compatible with JavaScript’s built-in Math library.</p>\n<h3 id=\"4-momentdate-fns\"><a href=\"#4-momentdate-fns\" aria-label=\"4 momentdate fns permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>4. Moment/date-fns</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/moment/moment\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Moment</a> - moment.js is a JavaScript date and time manipulation library for parsing, validating, manipulating, and formatting dates.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/date-fns/date-fns\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Date-fns</a> - Date-fns is a growingly popular (11K stars, over half a million weekly NPM installs) time manipulation library for Javascript, chosen by many developers to replace moment.js (see comparison) providing over 130 functions to manipulate dates in the browser and Node.js.</p>\n<h3 id=\"5-sugar\"><a href=\"#5-sugar\" aria-label=\"5 sugar permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>5. Sugar</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/andrewplummer/Sugar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sugar</a> - Sugar is a Javascript utility library for working with native objects.</p>\n<h3 id=\"6-lazy\"><a href=\"#6-lazy\" aria-label=\"6 lazy permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>6. Lazy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/dtao/lazy.js\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lazy</a> - lazy.js is a functional utility library for JavaScript with a lazy engine that “strives to do as little work as possible” while still being flexible enough.</p>\n<h3 id=\"7-collectjs\"><a href=\"#7-collectjs\" aria-label=\"7 collectjs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>7. CollectJS</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/ecrmnn/collect.js\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">CollectJS</a> - collect.js is a very promising and dependency free wrapper for working with arrays and objects in Javascript with dozens of useful functionalities in and API which is (almost) identical to Laravel Collections</p>\n<h3 id=\"8-chancejs\"><a href=\"#8-chancejs\" aria-label=\"8 chancejs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>8. ChanceJS</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/chancejs/chancejs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ChanceJS</a> - Chance is a minimalist generator of random strings, numbers, etc. to help reduce some monotony, while writing automated tests or anywhere else you need anything random.</p>\n<h3 id=\"9-chartjs\"><a href=\"#9-chartjs\" aria-label=\"9 chartjs permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>9. ChartJS</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/chartjs/Chart.js\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ChartJS</a> - chart.js is a great example of how sometimes less is more with 8 different data visualization types, each of them animated and customizable.</p>\n<h3 id=\"10-polished\"><a href=\"#10-polished\" aria-label=\"10 polished permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>10. Polished</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/styled-components/polished\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Polished</a> - Polished is a great lightweight toolset for writing styles in JavaScript with Sass-style helper functions and mixins.</p>\n<h3 id=\"11-mout\"><a href=\"#11-mout\" aria-label=\"11 mout permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>11. Mout</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/mout/mout\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mout</a> - Mout.js is a collection of modular JavaScript utilities that can be used in the browser as AMD modules or on node.js, providing helper methods similar to those found on other languages standart libraries (Python, Ruby, PHP etc).</p>\n<h3 id=\"honourable-mentions\"><a href=\"#honourable-mentions\" aria-label=\"honourable mentions permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Honourable Mentions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/panzerdp/voca\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Voca</a> - A Javascript library for string manipulations.</p>\n<h4 id=\"licia\"><a href=\"#licia\" aria-label=\"licia permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Licia</h4>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/liriliri/licia\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Licia</a> - A simple collection of useful JavaScript snippets with high docs and test coverage with Zero dependencies.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://hackernoon.com/a-new-utility-library-designed-to-get-things-done-d203daa91429\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Licia Explanation Article</a></p>\n<p><strong>Other Reads:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.infoworld.com/article/3048833/brendan-eich-javascript-standard-library-will-stay-small.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Brenden Eich about Javascript Ecosystem</a></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"11 JavaScript Utility Libraries you Should Know in 2019","date":"September 05, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/javascript-utility-libraries-you-should-know/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/pure-css-animation-inspiration-on-codepen/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Inspiration-10 Examples of Pure CSS Animation on CodePen"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/javascript-animation-libraries-you-should-know/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"11 JavaScript Animation Libraries For 2019"}}}}}